<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[227,348,1773,1799]" box="[227,348,1773,1799]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,1773,1799]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,1773,1799]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[227,1437,1819,1951]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[356,544,1819,1845]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroborineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[356,544,1819,1845]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Stroborineceras</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[552,659,1820,1846]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with depressed, rounded-triangular whorl profile (ww/wh ~1.50), venter strongly flattened, ventrolateral shoulder subangular with sharp longitudinal ridges. Whorls not embracing. Ornament with fine spiral ridges in the submarginal ventral position; five or six spiral ridges are located on the flank.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[227,957,1989,2063]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[227,362,1989,2015]" box="[227,362,1989,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,362,1989,2015]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="75" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,362,1989,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[227,957,2036,2063]" box="[227,957,2036,2063]" pageId="8" pageNumber="75">Named after the town of In Salah in the central Sahara Desert.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
