<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[227,372,640,666]" box="[227,372,640,666]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,640,666]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,640,666]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[227,1437,686,959]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,686,712]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Holotype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30445.1 is a whorl fragment of about 90 degrees angular length, consisting of the last chambers of the phragmocone and part of the body chamber (
<figureCitation box="[962,1054,722,748]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[227,270,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[317,1347,1055,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-222@9.[309,1355,1050,1923]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6. Stroborineceras insalahensis gen. et sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype MB.C.30445.2. B. Holotype MB.C.30445.1. C. Paratype MB.C.30445.3. D. Paratype MB.C.30446.1. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902599" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902599/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
). The maximum whorl height is 
<quantity box="[228,310,757,783]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
. The whorl profile is rounded-triangular and depressed (ww/wh = 1.51) with a flattened venter and an almost semi-circular area encompassing the flanks and dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1114,792,818]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[227,270,1893,1919]" captionTargetBox="[266,1396,1381,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-361@10.[266,1396,1381,1859]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 7. Stroborineceras insalahensis gen. et sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30445.1. B. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30446.1. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30445.3. D. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30445.2. E. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30445.1, at ww =15.3 mm, wh=10.2 mm. F. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30445.3, at ww =15.1 mm, wh =9.8 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902601/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
); the ventrolateral shoulder is subangular. The specimen bears at least eight longitudinal lines, two of which are on the edge of the venter and six on the flank. The suture line shows a broad, almost semi-circular external lobe, a tightly rounded ventrolateral saddle and a shallow and very broad lateral lobe. On the dorsum the suture line shows an almost straight course (
<figureCitation box="[617,709,933,959]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[227,270,1893,1919]" captionTargetBox="[266,1396,1381,1859]" captionTargetId="figure-361@10.[266,1396,1381,1859]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 7. Stroborineceras insalahensis gen. et sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30445.1. B. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30446.1. C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30445.3. D. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30445.2. E. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30445.1, at ww =15.3 mm, wh=10.2 mm. F. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30445.3, at ww =15.1 mm, wh =9.8 mm. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902601" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902601/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[227,1436,998,1130]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
The 
<typeStatus box="[281,393,999,1025]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">paratypes</typeStatus>
illustrate that the variation is quite low; all specimens show very similar whorl profiles, ornament and suture line. Compared to the 
<typeStatus box="[786,892,1033,1059]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">holotype</typeStatus>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[961,1062,1034,1060]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30445.2 (
<figureCitation box="[1275,1374,1033,1059]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[227,270,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[317,1347,1055,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-222@9.[309,1355,1050,1923]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6. Stroborineceras insalahensis gen. et sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype MB.C.30445.2. B. Holotype MB.C.30445.1. C. Paratype MB.C.30445.3. D. Paratype MB.C.30446.1. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902599" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902599/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Fig. 6A</figureCitation>
) has more strongly developed spiral lines on the flanks and the 
<typeStatus box="[958,1070,1069,1095]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">paratypes</typeStatus>
MB.C.30445.3 (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1374,1069,1095]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[227,270,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[317,1347,1055,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-222@9.[309,1355,1050,1923]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6. Stroborineceras insalahensis gen. et sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype MB.C.30445.2. B. Holotype MB.C.30445.1. C. Paratype MB.C.30445.3. D. Paratype MB.C.30446.1. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902599" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902599/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) and MB.C.30446.1 (
<figureCitation box="[418,509,1104,1130]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[227,270,1965,1991]" captionTargetBox="[317,1347,1055,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-222@9.[309,1355,1050,1923]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 6. Stroborineceras insalahensis gen. et sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (all Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Paratype MB.C.30445.2. B. Holotype MB.C.30445.1. C. Paratype MB.C.30445.3. D. Paratype MB.C.30446.1. Scale bar units =1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902599" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902599/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Fig. 6D</figureCitation>
) show slightly more distinct submarginal ridges on the venter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[227,341,1169,1195]" box="[227,341,1169,1195]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,341,1169,1195]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,341,1169,1195]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[227,1437,1216,1348]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[227,567,1216,1242]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroborineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="insalahensis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[227,567,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">Stroborineceras insalahensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[574,750,1216,1242]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[905,983,1216,1242]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroborineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[905,983,1216,1242]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">S. felis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[990,1166,1216,1242]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the more depressed whorl profile (ww/wh = 
<quantity box="[507,589,1251,1278]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.937" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="in" value="1.55">1.55 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[596,771,1251,1277]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroborineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="insalahensis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[596,771,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">S. insalahensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[778,955,1252,1278]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
but only 
<quantity box="[1068,1149,1251,1278]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.175" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" unit="in" value="1.25">1.25 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[1157,1235,1251,1277]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroborineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1157,1235,1251,1277]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="77">S. felis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1243,1420,1252,1278]" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), by the flattened or weakly convex venter (concave in 
<taxonomicName authority="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel, 2022" authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[867,946,1286,1313]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Stroborineceras" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="10" pageNumber="77" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felis" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
